# agent-ops loop (stageverify)

This repo uses the **agent-ops** skill (`~/.cursor/skills/agent-ops`, git `C:\Projects\cursor-agent-brain`).

## Orchestration profile

- **Profile:** `composer-default` (overrides SKILL.md §10 Sonnet-default)
- **Trials:** `.cursor/trials.json` (per-project)
- **Authority:** This file wins on orchestration; SKILL.md wins on outcome schema and tier table.
- **Session start / pre-edit / model routing:** `composer-orchestrator.mdc` + `model-gates.mdc` — do not duplicate here.

## During work

- **Windows shell:** use `cmd /c dir` (not `Get-ChildItem` / `ls`) — PowerShell pipeline output unreliable in Cursor terminal capture.
- **Shell backend can die mid-session** (observed 3× on 2026-07-08): if shell commands return no results after 1–2 retries, do NOT stall or fail — fall back to Read/Glob/Grep for measurements and file checks; defer git/npm to the parent session or a later retry; report the caveat. If the task REQUIRES shell (commit/push/deploy/validate), STOP and report the blocker. Detail: `gotcha-map.json` → `subagent-shell-unavailable`.
- **STATS.md is stale:** `cursor-agent-brain/STATS.md` regenerated nightly — count actual `.jsonl` files in `outcomes/` for Phase-2 readiness.

## Session end (MANDATORY when substantive — do not skip)

Append ONE outcome line to brain repo, then commit+push. PowerShell:

```powershell
$m = $env:COMPUTERNAME
$row = '{"date":"<YYYY-MM-DD>","repo":"stageverify","archetype":"<slug>","model":"<slug>","tier":"<T?>","confStart":<n>,"confAfter":<n>,"outcome":"ok","machine":"'+$m+'","note":"<=80 chars"}'
Add-Content -Path "C:\Projects\cursor-agent-brain\outcomes\$m.jsonl" -Value $row
cd "C:\Projects\cursor-agent-brain"; git add outcomes; git commit -m "log: <archetype> <model>"; git push
```

- `archetype` = slug from `archetypes.json`. `outcome` = ok | fail | escalate.
- Skip trivial/no-signal turns.

## stageverify vs brain commits

Stageverify code → stageverify repo. One outcome line → brain repo. Keep pushes separate.
